                        "text": "SEND this to your favourite coffee lover!\n\nYou can thank us later \ud83d\ude09\n\nFor the ultimate coffee experience, you need this spot on your Tokyo itinerary. Heck it\u2019s worth booking a Japan trip just to come here!\n\n\ud83d\udccc Koffee Mameya Kakeru \n(their Kiyosumi Shirakawa location, not the one in Shibuya as they have different concepts) \n\nYou can choose one of their 3 omakase menus. Or go a la carte (their espresso martini and cheesecake are supposed to be *amazing*)\n\n\ud83d\udcb0 Prices start at \u00a56,500 and go up to \u00a510,000 ($42-65) for the tasting menu so it\u2019s not a cheap experience for our fellow mid-budget travellers. But, as coffee lovers, we thought it was worth every penny\n\nThe baristas seriously know what they\u2019re about and their coffee/food pairing were sensational \n\n\ud83d\udce2 Just make sure to book in advance as they don\u2019t have many seats \n\n\u2014\u2014\n\nWhat to do in Tokyo | Tokyo cafes | Tokyo coffee shops | Japanese coffee culture | Where to eat in Tokyo | Unique things to do in Tokyo | Bougie backpacking | Travel in your 30s | Specialty coffee | Panama geisha coffee | #tokyorestaurant #travelfoodie #ineedcoffee #specialtycoffee #japantrip #koffeemameya"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
